article.description: — Ryan Davis had 21 points as Vermont won its ninth straight game, topping Maine 81-68 on Saturday.
article.headline: Davis scores 21 to lift Vermont over Maine 81-68
article.linkText: Davis scores 21 to lift Vermont over Maine 81-68
article.story: BURLINGTON, Vt. -- — Ryan Davis had 21 points as Vermont won its ninth straight game, topping Maine 81-68 on Saturday. Ben Shungu had 19 points for Vermont (15-4, 7-0 America East Conference). Justin Mazzulla added 10 points. Finn Sullivan had seven rebounds. Vukasin Masic had 17 points for the Black Bears (4-15, 1-7). Ja'Shonte Wright-McLeish added 15 points. Maks Klanjscek had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
